Date: 1992-05-18

Title: The Quantum Double in Integrable Quantum Field Theory

Authors: D. Bernard and A. LeClair

Comments: 43 pages

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B399 (1993) 709-748

Various aspects of recent works on affine quantum group symmetry ofintegrable 2d quantum field theory are reviewed and further clarified. Ageometrical meaning is given to the quantum double, and other properties ofquantum groups. Multiplicative presentations of the Yangian double areanalyzed.